Market Analysis and Insights
Global Food Salt Market
Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global food salt market to be growing at a CAGR of 2.8% in the forecast period of 2022-2029.
Food salt is a type of salt specifically added to enhance the flavor of foods. In addition to improving taste, it also helps preserve food by inhibiting the growth of microorganisms, thereby preventing spoilage.
The growing global demand for organic food has significantly increased the use of food salt, particularly in the form of nutraceutical supplements, which will continue to drive the food salt market. Additionally, the high demand for gourmet salt and the rising adoption of vacuum pan technology in salt production are key macroeconomic factors positively impacting the global food salt market. Other contributing factors include heightened awareness of the health benefits of food salt and increased consumer spending on food and beverages, which will support the market's growth. Moreover, the growing use of food salt in dressings and seasonings is expected to further accelerate market expansion. As the number of applications increases and lifestyle changes continue, the food salt market is poised for continued growth.
Moreover, the rise in the focus on healthy lifestyle and upsurge in the number of restaurants will boost the beneficial opportunities for the growth of food salt market. Additionally, rising production of salt warm pads in medical and industrial use and development of flavored salt will act as major driver and further create new opportunities for market’s growth in the above mentioned forecast period.
However, high cost associated with packaging, processing, labelling and marketing will hamper the market growth rate. Additionally, the impact of COVID-19 pandemic on the manufacturing units and supply chain will obstruct the food salt market's overall growth. Also, contribution of salt to high blood pressure, heart failure, kidney problems, stroke, osteoporosis and fluid retention will challenge the food salt market throughout the forecast period.
